# Automation System Architecture

**Last Updated:** November 14, 2025
**Status:** 📋 Planned (Q2 2026 - Sprint 2 Phase 2)
**Purpose:** Local-first automation engine with Trigger → Condition → Action model
**Audience:** Engineering, Product

---

## Overview

Neuman Brain's automation system enables users to create declarative rules that automate repetitive workflows across tasks, events, and other entities. The system operates offline-first using Service Worker timers and IndexedDB storage, with optional cloud syncing.

### Goals

**Primary:**
- **Declarative Rules** - Simple Trigger → Conditions → Actions model
- **Offline-First** - Works completely offline using Service Worker and IndexedDB
- **Safe Execution** - Idempotent actions, loop protection, rate limits, audit logging
- **Portable** - Rules serialize to JSON and sync across devices
- **Competitive Parity** - Match features from Trello Butler, Asana Rules, Monday.com Automations

**Non-Goals (v1):**
- Cross-workspace automations (single workspace only)
- Arbitrary user scripts (declarative actions only for security)
- Server-side execution (client-side only)

---

## Competitive Context

### Feature Parity Targets

| Platform | Automation Features | Access Level | Our Approach |
|----------|-------------------|--------------|--------------|
| **Trello Butler** | Rules, buttons, scheduled commands | Premium+ | Free, offline-capable |
| **Asana Rules** | Triggers and actions | Starter tier (limited) | Free, full feature set |
| **Monday.com** | No-code rules, action caps | Varies by plan | Free, unlimited actions |

**Key Differentiator:** All competitors require internet connection. Our automations work offline and sync when online.

---

## Architecture

### System Components

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    User Interface                        │
│  - Rule Builder UI (visual editor)                      │
│  - Preset Library (templates)                           │
│  - Run History Viewer                                   │
└───────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                    │
┌───────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 Automation Engine                        │
│  - Trigger Evaluator                                    │
│  - Condition Matcher                                    │
│  - Action Executor                                      │
│  - Loop Prevention                                      │
│  - Rate Limiter                                         │
└───────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                    │
┌───────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  Storage Layer                           │
│  - IndexedDB: automations, runs, schedules, queue       │
│  - OPFS: JSONL run logs (/automations/logs/*.jsonl)    │
└───────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                    │
┌───────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 Service Worker                           │
│  - Background trigger evaluation                        │
│  - Cron alarm scheduler                                 │
│  - Action execution in background                       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Execution Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant UI
    participant DB as IndexedDB
    participant SW as ServiceWorker

    UI->>DB: Commit new Task (transaction)
    DB-->>SW: Emit onCreate(Task) event
    SW->>SW: Evaluate all automation rules
    SW->>SW: Check conditions
    SW->>DB: Execute actions (single transaction)
    SW-->>UI: Notify via postMessage
    UI-->>UI: Update UI with changes
```

