## Safety & Performance

### Loop Prevention

**Problem:** Automation A triggers Automation B which triggers Automation A (infinite loop)

**Solution:** Windowed de-duplication
```typescript
interface LoopDetectionKey {
  ruleId: string;
  targetId: string;
  mutationHash: string;  // Hash of field changes
}

// Cache recent executions (last 60 seconds)
// Reject if same (ruleId, targetId, mutationHash) seen recently
```

### Rate Limiting

**Per-Rule Limits:**
- Default: 60 actions/minute
- Burst: 10 actions in 10 seconds
- Configurable per automation

**Implementation:**
```typescript
interface RateLimit {
  automationId: string;
  windowStart: number;
  actionsInWindow: number;
  burstCount: number;
  burstWindowStart: number;
}
```

### Idempotency

All actions should be idempotent (safe to execute multiple times):
- `set`: Overwrites value (idempotent)
- `addTag`: No-op if tag exists (idempotent)
- `move`: No-op if already in target column (idempotent)
- `create`: Generate deterministic ID to prevent duplicates

