## Example Automations

### Example 1: Snooze Overdue Tasks to Next Weekday

**Use Case:** Automatically reschedule overdue tasks to next weekday at 9am

```json
{
  "id": "auto_snooze_overdue",
  "name": "Snooze overdue to next weekday 9am",
  "enabled": true,
  "scope": "global",
  "trigger": {
    "type": "onDue",
    "leadMinutes": 0
  },
  "conditions": [
    { "lhs": "status", "op": "!=", "rhs": "Done" }
  ],
  "actions": [
    { "type": "set", "field": "due", "value": "{{nextWeekdayAt(9, 'America/Detroit')}}" },
    { "type": "addTag", "tag": "overdue" },
    { "type": "notify", "target": "local", "message": "Task snoozed to next weekday" }
  ]
}
```

### Example 2: Auto-Archive Completed Tasks After 7 Days

**Use Case:** Keep Kanban board clean by archiving old completed tasks

```json
{
  "id": "auto_archive_done",
  "name": "Auto-archive Done after 7 days",
  "enabled": true,
  "scope": "board",
  "trigger": {
    "type": "cron",
    "expr": "0 2 * * *"
  },
  "conditions": [
    { "lhs": "status", "op": "==", "rhs": "Done" },
    { "lhs": "updatedAt", "op": "<=", "rhs": "{{now - 7d}}" }
  ],
  "actions": [
    { "type": "move", "to": "Archived" }
  ]
}
```

